node.text:
We have had our periods used to be gaslit in the past, to delegitimize our feelings and I think that it made us reluctant to discuss the real changes that are happening during that time. And knowing these things and really scrutinizing and documenting them to make your life as easy as possible is POWER. On my podcast we talk PMS and embracing the powers of it, whilst making space for the issues it can bring, we talk directing, we talk career, body image in this industry. Elizabeth is so strong and smart and inspiring. I think you’ll enjoy this episode.

node.text: According to The Body Shop's Self Love survey, over 40% of the LGBTQ+ community struggle with self-love - unacceptable! So in the spirit of Pride, inspired by @thebodyshop @lawrencechaney and @tiakofi, I took some time to remind my friend @munroebergdorf just how fabulous she is. I encourage all of you to share a kind or positive word to someone you know from the LGBTQ+ community and tag #SelfLoveUprising so that together we can spark a chain of collective self-love. And if you're in need of a pick me up or inspiration, check out 'The Reverse Roast' starring Lawrence Chaney and Tia Kofi over at @thebodyshop

Sorry I didn’t know you can’t remove the comedy filter once you’re live. I’m an idiot! 

Another fun and quick and simple exercise to brighten your day with my mate the lovely @aljacksonpt ❤️

Exercise doesn’t have to be for weight loss. It doesn’t have to be for muscle gain. It doesn’t have to be in skin tight clothing. It doesn’t have to be a way to relieve your guilt about food. You can snack, and dance and wear baggy clothing and just do it for your peace of mind.

We are taking exercise BACK from the clutches of diet culture. 

#mentalhealthawarenessmonth

node.text:
Sorry today’s workout wasn’t saved due to technical difficulties of IG live! My biggest fear WAS dancing in front of other people, until today... when that was replaced by dancing ALONE WITH NO MUSIC LIVE TO THE WORLD. Thanks for laughing along with me and sticking around for the whole thing. It was another great class, and the lovely messages are POURING IN once again in my DMS. I love you all. Fuck diet culture. We are taking exercise BACK. No compulsory tight clothing. No hunger. No pressure. No self hate. No self consciousness. Just joy, snacks, galloping and endorphins. 

See you next Saturday!

Me and my mate @aljacksonpt decided to do a mental health workout together. Baggy clothes. Snacks. No mirrors. No fear of the body. No pressure. Just good vibes. I was SO NERVOUS because I’m not a great mover! And I’m afraid of IG lives! But you were all so sweet and supportive and by the end the happy chemicals in my brain took over and I didn’t care anymore. 

I hope you enjoyed. This was just the first one and we will work to figure out how to make it as great as possible for you. 

I hope you liked it. I’m still *slightly* shy about posting this to grid. But I’m really happy we did it and I want to change exercise culture to include everyone, and to be more about us serving ourselves, rather than working out to please others. 

😬😬😬😬😬

LOVE YOU! 

(Clearly)

Fucking weirdos. 

The trolling of Lizzo, and other mostly women, mostly mostly Black women, because she made a song that made her (and a lot of other people) happy…. Is deranged. We have lost the plot as a society. Nobody is forcing you to hear her music, look at her (wonderful) face or body, or hear her name. You choose to seek her out and be vile. If she was doing something cruel or problematic, fine, call her out. She. Made. A. Song. ABOUT PEOPLE BRINGING WOMEN DOWN. And you perfectly proved her right. And doubled down on your cruelty and piling on. And then when it made her cry, you laughed at her for crying about it. As if you have the fucking backbone to even try for your dreams. To even risk losing face or receiving criticism from anyone. As if you have a modicum of her light and charisma and courage… from your sofa with your little anonymous account? 

Get the fuck out of here.

Let the woman live.

Only sick people spend time going after innocent artists and not actual oppressors/abusers/criminals online. 

If you don’t like her music, listen to something else: there are 9 zillion songs available.

Oh. My. GOD. 

Wow, I found a pic I took of my screen test from 14 years ago when I auditioned for T4 on Channel 4 to be a host alongside @rickedwards1 I cannot believe I lasted in this industry this long. I really thought they would fire me after two weeks tops. I didn’t even quit my day job as a teacher for like 6 months into this national TV job, because I was so sure it was a terrible mix up. 

I have never had a plan, or known what I’m doing until I’m doing it, but I never gave up. Even when I have been told to by a lot of people. Women are not encouraged to just keep going. 

So I am telling you to just KEEP going. Nobody gets to decide when you stop growing, apart from you. 

We persist. 

Good luck in whatever brave endeavor you’re embarking upon! I’m on the sidelines cheering you on, FUCKING ESPECIALLY when you fall down. 

Get up, toss your hair, and try again. ❤️

node.text:
Please read:

Remember my IG highlight about media GASLIGHTING against women?

Example 10,000.

Yesterday a trailer dropped for a new teen remake. I joked that it looks terrible but that we’re all gonna watch it and make it number one. Because that’s what we do. (See also: Tiger King.) 

This got turned into a serious attack from me, as if I actually give a flying fuck about a teen rom com. I’m IN a cheesy teen rom com coming out later in the year which people will probably also bemoan. Who cares? These movies are not supposed to be Shakespeare. 

The REASON this is important is because it isn’t just a 1000th example of the tabloids exaggerating my response to something trivial. It’s WHY. It’s a designed tactic to turn everything I say into serious hysteria, SO THAT it dilutes my “outrage” across so many subjects so that when I speak about things that actually MATTER, things our white conservative bigoted tabloid media don’t like me raising awareness on, ie: abortion rights, trans rights, mental health, misogyny and MOSTLY diet cultures - they get most of their funding from diet companies…. People won’t listen because they’ll just be like “oh god what’s she banging on about this time?” 

They overexpose me to discredit me and make me look hysterical about everything so that when I’m actually hysterical about human rights being taken away, it’s easier to dismiss and blend in with other things. 

You mostly know me as someone deeply silly and tongue in cheek who cares a lot about equality. But generally on the internet I have the reputation of being this super serious, aggressive, overly emotional, self righteous, incessantly aggravated, preaching maniac. This is DESIGNED by the tabloids who I threaten with my work towards progressive policy. They do this to every woman who speaks about any subject they fear. And it works because the public don’t know how coded this all is. 

They also do it so that I’ll be too exasperated by their constant twisting of my words, to speak any more. Not gonna happen. 

Watch them ignore this actual “SLAM” And “BLAST” and look out for when they do this to strong brown and especially Black women.

It’s laced with malicious intention.
